   "source": [
    "# Notebook 14 — Genome Assembly: Overlap Graphs and De Bruijn Graphs\n",
    "\n",
    "**Module:** 08 — Bioinformatics: Sequence Analysis  \n",
    "**Notebook:** 14 of 18  \n",
    "**Time estimate:** 75 minutes\n",
    "\n",
    "> De Bruijn graph assembly is the algorithmic foundation of every modern\n",
    "> short-read assembler (SPAdes, Velvet, SOAPdenovo). Know the k-mer graph\n",
    "> construction and why it's used instead of overlap graphs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 1 — Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "A genome sequencer produces millions of short reads. The assembly problem: reconstruct\n",
    "the original genome sequence from the reads. This is analogous to reassembling a\n",
    "shredded book from its fragments. Two main algorithmic approaches exist: overlap\n",
    "graphs (OLC) and De Bruijn graphs (DBG). Modern short-read assemblers use DBG."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 2 — Intuition\n",
    "\n",
    "**Overlap-Layout-Consensus (OLC):**\n",
    "- Build a graph where each read is a node\n",
    "- Edges connect reads that overlap by a minimum length\n",
    "- Find a Hamiltonian path through the graph (visits each node exactly once)\n",
    "- Problem: O(n²) pairwise overlap computation; Hamiltonian path is NP-hard\n",
    "\n",
    "**De Bruijn Graph (DBG):**\n",
    "- Break reads into all k-mers (overlapping k-length substrings)\n",
    "- Nodes are (k-1)-mers; edges are k-mers (an edge from prefix to suffix of each k-mer)\n",
    "- Assembly = Eulerian path through the graph (visits each edge exactly once)\n",
    "- Eulerian path can be found in O(E) — polynomial, not NP-hard\n",
    "- Advantage: compact representation; naturally handles repetitive sequences"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 3 — Biological Background\n",
    "\n",
    "**Why assembly is hard:**\n",
    "- Repeats: if the same sequence appears multiple times, the assembler can't tell where\n",
    "  a read belongs\n",
    "- Coverage variation: some regions are over/under-represented in sequencing\n",
    "- Sequencing errors: a single error in a k-mer creates a spurious node in the DBG\n",
    "- k must be chosen carefully: too small = ambiguous paths; too large = gaps from errors\n",
    "\n",
    "**Long reads (PacBio, Oxford Nanopore) vs. short reads (Illumina):**\n",
    "- Long reads span repeats → overlap graph approach works better\n",
    "- Short reads: DBG approach (SPAdes, Velvet)\n",
    "- Hybrid assembly: use long reads to scaffold short-read assembly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## Step 4 — Mathematical Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "**De Bruijn Graph construction:**\n",
    "1. Extract all k-mers from all reads\n",
    "2. For each k-mer $K = b_1 b_2 \\ldots b_k$:\n",
    "   - Add node $b_1 \\ldots b_{k-1}$ (prefix, length $k-1$)\n",
    "   - Add node $b_2 \\ldots b_k$ (suffix, length $k-1$)\n",
    "   - Add directed edge: prefix → suffix, labelled with $K$\n",
    "3. Assembly = Eulerian path (traverses each edge exactly once)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Eulerian path exists iff:**\n",
    "- At most one node has (out-degree - in-degree = 1) → start node\n",
    "- At most one node has (in-degree - out-degree = 1) → end node\n",
    "- All other nodes have equal in-degree and out-degree\n",
    "- Graph is connected\n",
    "\n",
    "**k-mer complexity:**\n",
    "- Total k-mers = (read_length - k + 1) × n_reads\n",
    "- Distinct k-mers limited by 4^k for DNA\n",
    "- Typical k: 21–127 for Illumina assembly"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 6 — Python Implementation\n",
    "from __future__ import annotations\n",
    "from collections import defaultdict\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from typing import Optional\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def extract_kmers(sequence: str, k: int) -> list[str]:\n",
    "    return [sequence[i:i+k] for i in range(len(sequence) - k + 1)]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_debruijn(reads: list[str], k: int) -> dict[str, list[str]]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Build De Bruijn graph.\n",
    "    Returns adjacency list: {node (k-1 mer): [list of successor nodes]}\n",
    "    Each edge corresponds to a k-mer in the reads.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    graph = defaultdict(list)\n",
    "    edge_kmers = defaultdict(list)  # (u, v) -> k-mer labels\n",
    "\n",
    "    all_kmers = []\n",
    "    for read in reads:\n",
    "        if len(read) >= k:\n",
    "            all_kmers.extend(extract_kmers(read, k))\n",
    "\n",
    "    for kmer in all_kmers:\n",
    "        prefix = kmer[:-1]   # first k-1 chars\n",
    "        suffix = kmer[1:]    # last k-1 chars\n",
    "        graph[prefix].append(suffix)\n",
    "        if prefix not in graph:\n",
    "            graph[prefix] = []\n",
    "        if suffix not in graph:\n",
    "            graph[suffix] = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    return dict(graph)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def graph_degrees(graph: dict[str, list[str]]) -> dict[str, dict]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Compute in-degree and out-degree for each node.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    nodes = set(graph.keys())\n",
    "    for neighbors in graph.values():\n",
    "        nodes.update(neighbors)\n",
    "\n",
    "    out_deg = {n: len(graph.get(n, [])) for n in nodes}\n",
    "    in_deg = {n: 0 for n in nodes}\n",
    "    for node, neighbors in graph.items():\n",
    "        for nb in neighbors:\n",
    "            in_deg[nb] += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    return {n: {'in': in_deg[n], 'out': out_deg[n]} for n in nodes}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def find_eulerian_path(graph: dict[str, list[str]]) -> Optional[list[str]]:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Hierholzer's algorithm for Eulerian path.\n",
    "    Returns list of nodes in path order, or None if no Eulerian path exists.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    # Make a mutable copy\n",
    "    adj = {node: list(neighbors) for node, neighbors in graph.items()}\n",
    "    # Add missing nodes\n",
    "    for neighbors in graph.values():\n",
    "        for nb in neighbors:\n",
    "            if nb not in adj:\n",
    "                adj[nb] = []\n",
    "\n",
    "    degrees = graph_degrees(graph)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Find start node: prefer node with out-degree - in-degree = 1\n",
    "    start = None\n",
    "    for node, deg in degrees.items():\n",
    "        if deg['out'] - deg['in'] == 1:\n",
    "            start = node\n",
    "            break\n",
    "    if start is None:\n",
    "        # Eulerian circuit: start anywhere\n",
    "        start = next(iter(adj))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Hierholzer's algorithm\n",
    "    stack = [start]\n",
    "    path = []\n",
    "    while stack:\n",
    "        v = stack[-1]\n",
    "        if adj.get(v):\n",
    "            u = adj[v].pop(0)\n",
    "            stack.append(u)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            path.append(stack.pop())\n",
    "    path.reverse()\n",
    "    return path\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def path_to_sequence(path: list[str]) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Reconstruct sequence from De Bruijn path.\n",
    "    Each node is a (k-1)-mer; concatenate the last character of each node.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    if not path:\n",
    "        return ''\n",
    "    seq = path[0]\n",
    "    for node in path[1:]:\n",
    "        seq += node[-1]\n",
    "    return seq\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def overlap_assembly(reads: list[str], min_overlap: int = 3) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Simple OLC: greedy assembly by maximum overlap.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    def overlap_length(s1, s2, min_len):\n",
    "        for i in range(len(s1), min_len - 1, -1):\n",
    "            if s2.startswith(s1[-i:]):\n",
    "                return i\n",
    "        return 0\n",
    "\n",
    "    assembled = reads[0]\n",
    "    remaining = list(reads[1:])\n",
    "    while remaining:\n",
    "        best_overlap = 0\n",
    "        best_read = None\n",
    "        for r in remaining:\n",
    "            ov = overlap_length(assembled, r, min_overlap)\n",
    "            if ov > best_overlap:\n",
    "                best_overlap = ov\n",
    "                best_read = r\n",
    "        if best_read is None or best_overlap == 0:\n",
    "            assembled += remaining[0]\n",
    "            remaining.pop(0)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            assembled += best_read[best_overlap:]\n",
    "            remaining.remove(best_read)\n",
    "    return assembled\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Demonstration: assemble a short sequence from reads\n",
    "true_sequence = 'ATCGATCGATCGATCG'\n",
    "k = 4\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simulate reads (every 3-base window = perfect coverage)\n",
    "reads = [true_sequence[i:i+6] for i in range(0, len(true_sequence)-5, 3)]\n",
    "print(f\"True sequence: {true_sequence}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Reads (k={6}, stride=3): {reads}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "graph = build_debruijn(reads, k)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nDe Bruijn graph (k={k}):\")\n",
    "for node, successors in sorted(graph.items()):\n",
    "    if successors:\n",
    "        print(f\"  {node} -> {successors}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "degrees = graph_degrees(graph)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNode degrees:\")\n",
    "for node, deg in sorted(degrees.items()):\n",
    "    marker = ''\n",
    "    if deg['out'] - deg['in'] == 1: marker = ' ← start'\n",
    "    if deg['in'] - deg['out'] == 1: marker = ' ← end'\n",
    "    print(f\"  {node}: in={deg['in']}, out={deg['out']}{marker}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "path = find_eulerian_path(graph)\n",
    "if path:\n",
    "    assembled = path_to_sequence(path)\n",
    "    print(f\"\\nEulerian path nodes: {' -> '.join(path[:5])} ... ({len(path)} nodes)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Assembled sequence:  {assembled}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"True sequence:       {true_sequence}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Match: {assembled == true_sequence}\")"
   ]
  },
